sentences: Mark Crew (born 21 February 1985) is a songwriter, record producer, and mix engineer based in London, known for
Crew produced the albums Bad Blood (UK #1, 3x platinum sales award; US #11, 1x platinum sales award), Wild World (UK #1, 1x gold; US #4) and Doom Days (UK #4; US #5) for Bastille.
The albums included the notable singles "Pompeii" (UK #2, 3x platinum; US #5, 6x platinum), "Of the Night" (UK #2, 1x platinum), and "Good Grief" (UK #13, 1x platinum; US #40).
One track from these mixtapes, "Of the Night", was the launch single for the extended version of the album, All This Bad Blood.
